late the philosophical and legal aspects of rights into more practical terms and applications. Regionally, the book draws on municipalities from across Canada while also making broad international comparisons. Scholars, policy makers, and activists with an interest in urban studies, planning, and law will find much of value throughout this volume. Contributors: Sandeep Agrawal, Rachelle Alterman, Sasha Best, Alexandra Flynn, Eran S. Kaplinsky, Ola P. Malik, Jennifer A. Orange, Michelle L. Oren, Renée Vaugeois. Afterword by Benjamin Davy  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLaw & Legal Studies / Law & Society. 4aLaw & Legal Studies. 4aPolitical Science / Municipal Politics. 4aPolitical Science. 4aUrban Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh  aFirst Nations.  aHenri Lefebvre.  aJohn Humphrey Centre for Peace and Human Rights.  acity council.  acivil society.  acollective rights.  acommunity.  adevelopment.  ahomeless.  alaw.  alawyer.  amarginalized.  aminority.  amunicipal government.  apolicy.  aurban planner.1 aAgrawal, Sandeep, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAgrawal, Sandeep, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAlterman, Rachelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBest, Sasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavy, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplinsky, Eran S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalik, Ola P., econtributor.4ctb4https://